annotationA: Iron regulatory protein 1B (Irp-1B) is a cytosolic aconitase. Although highly homologous to Irp-1A, the ability of Irp-1B to bind to highly conserved Iron Regulatory Elements has been questioned; Belongs to the aconitase/IPM isomerase family
annotationB: Citrate (Si)-synthase activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: citrate metabolic process; tricarboxylic acid cycle; cellular carbohydrate metabolic process
